column5: 162 and a wakeup and 191 and a wakeup, respectively, to Frog Rapids Camp and Lac Seul!!

That would be Perrault Lake Camp,...Mark and Amy Tycholis run that camp. It on the right just b4 Rainbow Point. I've been fishing this lake for about 4 years now and it's been great so far,...heard a lot of people call it the Dead Sea,....but if a 4 year newbie can catch all kinds of fish,...then I'd hate to see what I'm capable of on a better lake!!! The only thing I don't like about it is there is no lake trout. But all I got to do is jump on the other side of 105 and hit cliff lake if I want to catch those!!! Chuck Bearfvr13
33 days. Going up for some ice fishing with a detour in Red Rock for a few days.

Back to Lac Seul for the first time in 9yrs. I've had to privilege to fish private water in the Woodland Caribou Prov Park the last 9 yrs with friends. This year will be with family on the west side of Lac Seul. Fishermans Cove had a last minute opening and we were lucky enough to swoop in. I've stayed at Fishermans Cove before. I've also stayed at Lac Seul lodge and Onaway, all of which are fairly close to one another. It'll be long boat rides to all things MacKenzie Bay.

Starting the count down on Auger Lake with MLO out of Armstrong Station, Ontario. First time to this lake and excited for the new adventure with a 5 star fly in service!Flying in for 7 days beginning Aug. 12th.Only 202 days left!Any advice or input from people who have fished Auger would be fantastic.Thanks
Late season can be pretty nice. Stable weather compared to spring, less bugs, and you might have a chance to see the Northern Lights too.
152 days until going to Cedar Lake. Staying at Northern Lights resort
141 days until we are back on Eagle Lake...if I can wait that long.
112 day wait until I touch down on Little Vermilion Lake. I've been there for a bunch of walleye openers. A huge bunch. Never had a bad opener.Lots of huge pike waiting for me.
4 weeks till the next ice trip. First open water at Rainy starting the Monday after Memorial Day. Haven't decided what comes next.

Due to popular demand, well at least one WC member, it's time for this year's Countdown Thread.How many days until you drop a line on your favorite walleye spot?!Happy New Year. And safe travels and tight lines
247 days, 21 hours, 33 minutes and 34 seconds until we leave for Birch Dale Lodge on Eagle Lake for our 29th year there!!!
222 days until we leave for Slate Falls Outposts Miniss Lake East outpost.
153 days until I drop a white jig into the Albany River.
I am sooo disappointed in you David. I was watching for this thread just after midnight. You are over eight hours late.....Happy New Year my friend.Pooch
Gary, I was counting walleyes in my sleep at midnight! Happy Healthy New Year for you and your family!
Miniss is a great lake! I had the privilege of fishing Miniss with Hidden Bay Lodge a couple of years ago. Some of the best fighting walleyes I have ever had the pleasure to catch! Have a great trip!
174 days until fly in with Pourvoirie Moselle, St. Anne Du Lac, Quebec to Lac Natakim. Seanik Erie, Pa
173 days to Perrault Lake!
Which outfitter are you using? How is the fishing?
